more_text: >
  As a web-based rich text editor, Rich Text runs directly in your browser.
  At the core of this rich text application is CKeditor, meaning you get a familiar editing experience.
  The formatting toolbar includes all the essentials: headings, bold, italic, bullet lists, links, and image insertion.
  Document structure is made easy with the automatic outline feature, which creates a clickable table of contents in a collapsible sidebar.
  You can open a document, share the link with teammates, and everyone edits together in real time.
  In practice, you get the same rich web editing experience as Google Docs, but without data collection or ads.
